  "dateModified": "2026-03-07",
  "datePublished": "2026-03-07",
  "description": "The process of splitting a mature plant\u0026rsquo;s root system into two or more separate plants, each with a portion of roots and stems or buds. Division works with plants that naturally form clumps or spreading root systems. It is used to propagate perennials, to spread a plant to new locations, or to rejuvenate an overcrowded clump whose growth has declined. Common plants propagated by division include chives, rhubarb, and strawberries.\n",
